sections.text:
Milk producers and personnel involved in the collection and transport and retail of milk should be trained as necessary and have appropriate skills in the areas listed below:

• health of animals and use of veterinary drugs;
• manufacturing and use of feeds (more specifically fermented feeds);
• herd management;
• hygienic milking;
• storage, handling, collection and transport of milk (cleaning of storage tanks, temperature requirements, sampling procedures, etc.);
• microbiological, chemical and physical hazards and their control measures.

